# Changelog


### v1.21.0
- New: version.hpp for compile-time version information.
- Fix: Changed arguments behavior on argv[0] to be more reasonable. Now empty() ignores argv[0].
- Add: arguments now supports --help and --version specific tag.
- Chg: arguments now returns a boolean value indicating whether the option was found or using the default value.
- New: arguments now supports defining a primary command (first non-option argument).
- New: bytearray added appendContainer for storage of STL containers with supported element types.
- New: wstring-string conversion is now present in platform header.
- New: logt now supports steady-clock timestamps, and timestamp consturction is exposed now if you need to use it.
- New: platform now provides "find executable in path" function for easier executable searching.
- New: engeneering module (header-only) for easier engineering predefined type formatting.
- Fix: bytearray is now safer and more explicit about its behavior. Some functions may bahave differently than before.
- New: process module for easier process management. (still in development)
- Fix: logt formatting module is now working correctly. (It had a bug before that is not showing the corrent thread and function name)
- New: added SharedCppLib2 API Standard definition (api.hpp).
- New: abstract module for virtual path resource access, like abstract path.
- Dep: Some of the features in ansiio module are now marked as deprecated, since they are simply not working.
- New: ini module for simple INI file parsing and writing.
- New: xml module for xml parsing and writing. still in development.
- New: html module for html parsing and writing. still in development.
- New: uri library for URI parsing and building.
- New: network module for easier network programming.
- Chg: Base64 module is now using bytearray for binary side instead of string.

### v1.20.0
- New: arguments library with template-based type-safe parameter parsing.
- New: arguments supports integral, floating-point, enum, and custom deserializable types.
- Opt: arguments parsing simplified using std::from_chars (46% code reduction).
- Opt: arguments now defaults to space-separated values (--option value), equals syntax optional.

### v1.19.0
- New: bytearray_view for efficient serialization/deserialization with cursor management.
- New: UTF-16, UTF-32, and Base64 encoding/decoding support for bytearray.
- New: xtoEscapedString() with enhanced escape sequences (\n, \t, \r, etc).
- New: safeString methods (toSafeString/asSafeString) for length-prefixed string serialization.
- Opt: Improved enum bit operators with underlying_type_t and noexcept.
- Opt: Fixed logf timestamp functions to use cross-platform localtime_r/localtime_s.

